timelineItems.name: NE Revolution
timelineItems.text: We're underway at BMO Field! Tune into ESPN2 or ESPN Deportes, or catch the radio call on @985TheSportsHub! #NERevs #TORvNE

timelineItems.desc: Robbie Findley (Toronto FC) hits the bar with a header from the center of the box.
timelineItems.title: CROSSBAR: Robbie Findley’s header bounces off the woodwork

timelineItems.desc: Attempt missed. Sebastian Giovinco (Toronto FC) right footed shot from outside the box is close, but misses the top left corner from a direct free kick.
timelineItems.title: CHANCE: Sebastian Giovinco whistles a free kick inches wide

timelineItems.name: Peter Galindo
timelineItems.text: Since #NERevs' 4-1 loss to #RBNY on July 11: 5W, 1D, 12GF-3GA. @rossoAnto & @JeffreyCarlisle warned everyone...

timelineItems.name: Jake Catanese
timelineItems.text: #NERevs and Tierney looking for a foul near the endline, won't get it and Caldwell wraps up Giovinco for a #TFC free kick. #TORvNE

timelineItems.name: Sean Maslin
timelineItems.text: Giovinco literally is an ant compared to Goncalves #TFCLive #NERevs #TORvNE

timelineItems.name: Stamper's Journal
timelineItems.text: so close for giovinco. #TFC #MLS

timelineItems.name: Kyle J. Silva
timelineItems.text: Giovinco has been such a fun player to watch this season #NERevs

timelineItems.name: Craig
timelineItems.text: Still don't like the short corner kick #NERevs

timelineItems.name: NE Revolution
timelineItems.text: 15' #NERevs 1 TFC 0 Giovinco has another go from 18 yards but it doesn't get far off his foot - @2Fast2Farrell is there to block. #TORvNE

timelineItems.name: BottjerRNO
timelineItems.text: New England clearly the superior "team" but the Atomic Ant could pull something out of this game for #TFC.

timelineItems.name: Jake Catanese
timelineItems.text: Jeremy Hall shields Giovinco and the ball out for a goal kick, picked that up very quickly from @Oneswitz. #NERevs #TORvNE

timelineItems.name: Jeremy Tod
timelineItems.text: Giovinco. He good. #TFC #TFClive

timelineItems.name: Rahul Vaidyanath
timelineItems.text: #Giovinco showing no sign of injury - simply an incredible dribbling sequence & cross - #TORvNE #MLS

timelineItems.name: Culture Vulture
timelineItems.text: Somehow Cadwell got spun and nutmegged at the same time by Giovinco. #TORvNE

timelineItems.name: Ari Carrillo
timelineItems.text: There's no way Giovinco is from this planet. He's unreal. #MLS #TORvNE

timelineItems.desc: It will be a critical match for placing in the Eastern Conference when Toronto FC and the New England Revolution meet for a third time this season at BMO Field on Sunday afternoon.
timelineItems.title: HIGHLIGHTS: Toronto FC vs New England Revolution | September 13, 2015

timelineItems.name: Brian O'Connell
timelineItems.text: Caldwell winning the ball back from Altidore tho #TORvNE

timelineItems.name: NESoccerToday.com
timelineItems.text: Osorio tries carrying the ball into the left side of the box and collides with Hall. TFC with a dangerous free kick #TORvNE

timelineItems.name: Brian O'Connell
timelineItems.text: These dangerous FKs are going to bite #NERevs in the butt if they don't cut it out. #TORvNE

timelineItems.name: Sara
timelineItems.text: #TFC http://t.co/j230cU3NCF

timelineItems.name: BottjerRNO
timelineItems.text: Dare I say, Findley bringing the goods for #TFC today

timelineItems.name: Read U.S. Soccer
timelineItems.text: Just 30 minutes until KO between Toronto and New England Revs at the BMO Field. We'll have full coverage! #TORvNE http://t.co/Qk6MPItIBS

timelineItems.name: Miles Halpine
timelineItems.text: Good to see Jones and Bunbury starting today. #NERevs #TORvNE

timelineItems.name: Matthew Doyle
timelineItems.text: Potentially a big moment for @NewYorkRedBulls Shield hopes w/ Jones getting suspended for Wednesday's match. #TORvNE

timelineItems.name: NoMayoBob
timelineItems.text: At the footy game. #TFC http://t.co/0AGnXGxtj0

timelineItems.name: Michael Leach
timelineItems.text: Wet day at BMO Field, Giovinco is starting while nursing an injury. I question the wisdom of this move. #TFC #TFCLive

timelineItems.name: Randy Narine
timelineItems.text: The good news is that it is barely raining. The bad news is that it feels very cold. Regardless, I'm here. #TFC http://t.co/wLrmtX8JWl

timelineItems.name: On Fuego for Diego
timelineItems.text: that was an automatic goal from last years Lee #nerevs

timelineItems.desc: Own Goal by Damien Perquis, Toronto FC.  Toronto FC 0, New England Revolution 1.
timelineItems.title: OWN GOAL: Damien Perquis turns a Bunbury cross into his own net

timelineItems.name: Dalen Cuff
timelineItems.text: Underway on ESPN vs TFC. 3 game this week for #NERevs. Squad rotation important. Bunbury 1st start since July 25th. https://t.co/EzbeUpvyfy

timelineItems.name: Jeff Teves
timelineItems.text: This might be the best I've ever seen #TFC play.

timelineItems.name: Lisa
timelineItems.text: A convert #TFCLive #TFC #BMOField @torontofc http://t.co/hN7G52KxHT

timelineItems.name: MLS Nerd
timelineItems.text: That was great from Gonçalves I thought that was a easy goal #NERevs

timelineItems.name: Julian Cardillo
timelineItems.text: Great defending by Farrell and JoGo there. Casually stopping both Robbie Findley and Michael Bradley. #NERevs #TORvNE

timelineItems.name: Laura Armstrong
timelineItems.text: Little more than 30 mins in, #TFC still down 1 - 0. A pacey game, both teams going for it. Have to think something will come for #TFC.

timelineItems.name: John Molinaro
timelineItems.text: Robbie Findlay again causing problems. This has been his best half for #TFC this season.

timelineItems.name: Brian O'Connell
timelineItems.text: Bunbury did not need to do that to Findley. Why? #TORvNE

timelineItems.desc: Goal!  Toronto FC 0, New England Revolution 2. Diego Fagundez (New England Revolution) right footed shot from outside the box to the top left corner.  Assisted by Lee Nguyen.
timelineItems.title: GOAL: Diego Fagundez curls a shot past Konopka

timelineItems.name: NESoccerToday.com
timelineItems.text: #TFC is dominating on the stat sheet - lead in shots 9-1, shots on goal 2-0, passing accuracy 88% to 66% and has 63.6% of possession #TORvNE

timelineItems.name: John Molinaro
timelineItems.text: After a slow start (thought he was partly culpable on the goal) Bradley having a commanding game for #TFC.

timelineItems.name: Sean Fahey
timelineItems.text: Diego has been on fire. Lee has been on fire. This team is playing so good right now. #NERevs

timelineItems.name: Rahul Vaidyanath
timelineItems.text: wow - great strike by Fagundez - just taking their chances and capitalizing on mistakes - very hard on #TFC to be down 0-2 #TORvNE #MLS

timelineItems.name: Mario Moretto
timelineItems.text: Beautifully worked. Great team goal, with perfect finish by @DiegoFagundez14. #NERevs

timelineItems.name: Dan Dickinson
timelineItems.text: Robbie Findlay with Miss Of The Year. #TORvNE

timelineItems.name: Andy Edwards
timelineItems.text: That's a chance that Robbie Findley specializes in missing. Fastest player on the field, until you need him to get to a spot. #TORvNE

timelineItems.name: bensfer window
timelineItems.text: I know we’re up 2-0 but I’d have liked some more midfield hustle on that counter. #NERevs

timelineItems.name: John Molinaro
timelineItems.text: For all of #TFC's pretty passing plays, fabulous dribbling sequences, and possession, they're down 2-0 at the half.

timelineItems.name: Alf De Blasis
timelineItems.text: It's been one of those games - #TFC throughly dominated through the 1st 45 but #NERevs capitalized on their only 2 chances of the half.

timelineItems.name: Matty Jollie
timelineItems.text: I think we can all agree that the current run of form can be attributed to Jay Heaps resting players for the U.S. Open Cup #NERevs

timelineItems.name: Mike Crampton
timelineItems.text: Should #TFC have scored? Yes. Was is predictable they'd concede? Yes. Can they still win? Yes. But "10 men running around" isn't a formation

timelineItems.name: Tim Donahoe
timelineItems.text: #TORvNE #NERevs #TFC This game thoroughly demonstrates that shooting and finishing is much more important than passing and dribbling.

timelineItems.name: NE Revolution
timelineItems.text: 46' #NERevs 2 TFC 0 Early chance for TFC as Giovinco's chip beats @b_shuttle, but @Oneswitz is there to clear off the line! #TORvNE

timelineItems.name: Rahul Vaidyanath
timelineItems.text: wow what a howler of a start for Perquis - already his 2nd mistake - latest one is an OG - #TORvNE 0-1 #MLS

timelineItems.name: Gareth Wheeler
timelineItems.text: Robbie Findley over the bar and just high. 3-4-3 for #TFC. Amazing. Love this. #TFCLive

timelineItems.name: NE Revolution
timelineItems.text: 49' #NERevs 2 TFC 0 TFC pressing again and Findley finds himself in down the right, but his low shot is wide of the far post. #TORvNE

timelineItems.name: The Soccer Bros
timelineItems.text: Robbie Findley has been far more effective than altidore all game long. #TFCvNER #torvne @mls

timelineItems.name: Julian Cardillo
timelineItems.text: One goal for Toronto will really tip the scales here. They've got the momentum. #TORvNE

timelineItems.name: Rob
timelineItems.text: I think Charlie Davies needs a couple of games not starting #NERevs black whole when he gets the ball currently

timelineItems.name: Shawna Howell
timelineItems.text: Well done Diego!! Probably saved a shot there from Giovinco #TORvNE

timelineItems.desc: Goal!  Toronto FC 1, New England Revolution 2. Robbie Findley (Toronto FC) header from the center of the box to the bottom right corner. Assisted by Justin Morrow.
timelineItems.title: GOAL: Robbie Findley hits his header off the post and in

timelineItems.name: Rahul Vaidyanath
timelineItems.text: finally Findley finishes on his fifth chance I believe - should be a cracking finish now #TORvNE 1-2 #MLS

timelineItems.name: Jake Catanese
timelineItems.text: Revs scoreless streak ends, about time as well, Findley should have a brace at this point. #NERevs #TORvNE

timelineItems.name: Andy Edwards
timelineItems.text: Pretty spectacular own goal scored by TFC there. Bunbury with the "assist." This thing's an absolute track meet so far. #TORvNE

timelineItems.name: JT Chang
timelineItems.text: Really feel like Agudelo needs to come in for Davies... anything to try to get a bit more possession #NERevs

timelineItems.name: Rudi Schuller
timelineItems.text: You still feel that the Revs could create something out of nothing, despite being wholly outplayed thus far in the second half. #TORvNE

timelineItems.name: Gareth Wheeler
timelineItems.text: #TFC is playing really well. Great response to falling behind early.

timelineItems.name: Pawcio
timelineItems.text: #TFC c'mon reds. http://t.co/6a6Il8KORg

timelineItems.name: Matthew Doyle
timelineItems.text: Jones is lucky. Shoulda been a 2nd yellow. #TORvNE

timelineItems.name: The Deadlock Victim
timelineItems.text: Daigo better be up off the bench at this point. #NERevs

timelineItems.name: Peter Galindo
timelineItems.text: #TFC's best centre-back this season (Eriq Zavaleta) still cannot get a run of starts. He should, really.

timelineItems.desc: Goal!  Toronto FC 1, New England Revolution 3. Kelyn Rowe (New England Revolution) right footed shot from the center of the box to the bottom left corner of goal.
timelineItems.title: GOAL: Kelyn Rowe picks up a ball in the box and fires it home

timelineItems.name: Adam M
timelineItems.text: There's way too much time left in this game. #NERevs look like they'll need a 3rd goal if they want a win

timelineItems.name: Jeremy Roque
timelineItems.text: Man, Bradley needs to clear that. #TFC

timelineItems.name: Ringo
timelineItems.text: Nguyen > Bradley Davies & Agudelo both > Altidore Unfortunately, Giovinco > everyone. #NERevs #TFC

timelineItems.name: Brian Sciaretta
timelineItems.text: Michael Bradley was having such a terrific half for #TFC and then he does that... Yikes #TORvNE

timelineItems.name: Matthew Doyle
timelineItems.text: Let's all remember that play when "But Nguyen doesn't defend!" is the excuse for him not getting a #USMNT call. #TORvNE

timelineItems.name: Adam Comeau
timelineItems.text: Konopka has looked very below average in todays game #TORvNE #TFCLive

timelineItems.name: The Deadlock Victim
timelineItems.text: Unless the score changes, MOTM = Farrell tonight. #NERevs

timelineItems.name: Kyle McCarthy
timelineItems.text: Interested in xG figure for #TORvNE, in case anyone runs one at the end of this game. #MLS

timelineItems.desc: Attempt saved. Diego Fagundez (New England Revolution) left footed shot from the center of the box is saved in the bottom right corner.
timelineItems.title: SAVE: Chris Konopka makes a diving stop to deny Fagundez

timelineItems.name: Ryan Lanigan
timelineItems.text: After good challenge from Caldwell, perfect thru ball into the channel from Jones. Bunbury did well to put it in a dangerous area. #NERevs

timelineItems.name: NESoccerToday.com
timelineItems.text: Revs with a great chance as they take advantage of a man down. Fagundez who only had the GK to beat, but shot was turned away #TORvNE

timelineItems.name: MLS Nerd
timelineItems.text: You'd think it'd be 4 with the amount of time and space Lee Nguyen was just given #TORvNE

timelineItems.name: Jake Catanese
timelineItems.text: Twellman says Hall having a bad game, defending for 75% of the time tends to do that. #NERevs

timelineItems.name: KevBrown
timelineItems.text: This defence will not get through the playoffs. No good scoring 6 and conceding 7 #TFCLive #TFC

timelineItems.name: Chris Goodwin
timelineItems.text: I guess there's something to be said for absorbing 75+ minutes of pressure while sacrificing all possession #NERevs

timelineItems.name: NESoccerToday.com
timelineItems.text: Giovinco draws a foul on Scott Caldwell just outside the box along the right baseline. TFC with a free kick coming #TORvNE

timelineItems.name: NE Revolution
timelineItems.text: 90'+ #NERevs 3 TFC 1 3 minutes of stoppage time work for everybody? No? Oh... Well, this is weird. Cus that's what we're in. #TORvNE

timelineItems.name: Michael Leach
timelineItems.text: #TFC fought all day to create chances and were thwarted. The opportunities they presented #NERevs, NE made good on. End of story. #TFCLive
